📚 What I Learned

From this challenge, I learned:
How HTTP cookies store client-side data
How web applications sometimes trust user-controlled cookies
How attackers can manipulate cookies using browser developer tools
Basic web exploitation techniques

🔐 Vulnerability
Client-side cookie manipulation
The application trusted the value stored in the cookie without proper validation.
This allowed users to change the cookie value and access hidden responses.

